<title>USA: Sallie Mae, American Express unit in $750 mln pact.</title>
<headline>Sallie Mae, American Express unit in $750 mln pact.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Student Loan Marketing Association, known as Sallie Mae, said Tuesday it has agreed to buy up to $750 million in education loans originated by American Express Educational Assurance Co, an American Express Co affiliate.</p>
<p>The loans in the three-year agreement will be originated by the American Express affiliate under the Federal Family Education Loan Program, the nation's largest educational loan facility, it said.</p>
